'From Squeak3.7 of ''4 September 2004'' [latest update: #5989] on 13 October 2004 at 4:13:52 pm'!"Change Set:		backwarCompatibleDepr-mdDate:			13 October 2004Author:			Marcus DenkerThis adds #backwardCompatibilityOnly: to Object. Thiscan be used instead of deprecated: to tag methods thatare deprecated but will be kept for compatibilityIt chnages Smalltalk>>version to use that."!!Object methodsFor: 'error handling' stamp: 'md 10/13/2004 15:59'!backwardCompatibilityOnly: anExplanationString	"Warn that the sending method has been deprecated. Methods that are tagt with #backwardCompatibility:	 are kept for compatibility."	Preferences showDeprecationWarnings ifTrue:		[Deprecation signal: thisContext sender printString, ' has been deprecated (but will be kept for compatibility). ', anExplanationString]! !!SystemDictionary methodsFor: 'sources, change log' stamp: 'md 10/13/2004 15:58'!version	"Answer the version of this release."	self backwardCompatibilityOnly: 'Use SystemVersion current version'.	^SystemVersion current version! !